reviews.headline: Too Thick even for my dry skin
reviews.comments: After 1 month of use this is NOT for me. I have DRY mature skin so I am use to applying a thicker, richer formulation but this one just doesn't spread well. After 1 month no difference. I am disappointed because of the cost, have had better results with less expensive creams, of which I will go back too. Also I wish I could upload a picture I took of a big gap in the container, it's an air pocket therefore product is missing.

reviews.comments: this cream made my skin so smooth and bouncy.

reviews.headline: Tight and Light
reviews.comments:
30- 40 Latina with acne. I stopped using since the dermatologist recommended Cerave 2 yrs ago. i went along with it to save money. But I am convinced like in all clinical trials, it is severely biased against indigenous skin tones and POC. somehow I keep coming back to Estee Lauder specifically for the night eye cream and this particular moisturizer. 
just 2 days and my face feels nourished, blemishes are gone, skin feels tight. It is great for my brown skin. 
It is true it is a little greasy, but how much are you all using? you really need to get used to using as little as possible as it goes a long way. I like to get the travel sizes because the moisturizer will stay fresh longer, plus somehow it comes out a few dollars less. 
Everyone from friends to partner to complete strangers have complimented my youthful look, except for the 2 years off this moisturizer. This stuff takes 10 years off at least from what I can tell. Give it a shot now!

reviews.headline: Strong smell
reviews.comments: I was really disappointed in the Estee Lauder Revitalizing Supreme+ Youth Power Cream Moisturizer. The perfume smell was so strong that I could not use it on my face.

reviews.headline: I LOVE THIS CREAM
reviews.comments: I've used Estée Lauder skincare all my life.  My favorite I'd Advanced Night Repair Serum.  My second favorite is this cream.  I'm 71 and have no wrinkles  - just some sagging.   This cream smells great and it's  special ingredients tightens the skin and makes it glow.  The texture is a marvelous gel cream and it glides onto the skin.  ULTA occasionally has it at 1/2 price!

reviews.headline: Meh… It doesn't moisturize my skin
reviews.comments: I really wanted to like this bc I LOVE Estee. But this did nothing for my skin. I even used the serum underneath. Clarins serum is what works

reviews.headline: Would definitely buy this again!
reviews.comments: I love the way it goes on and how it feels on my face. It softens my skin and helps with my dry skin.

reviews.headline: Obsessed!!!
reviews.comments: I have never used a more luxurious moisturizer. I got it as a sample and I had to run to buy the full size. It makes me look so youthful and my fine lines are GONE! I notice a massive difference in my appearance when I use this(only at night). I also use the advanced night repair serum which pairs well together. I have very sensitive combo skin. I'm super dry during the winter and oily diring the summer. Adding this to my skincare routine has completely transformed my skin. BUY IT! You will not regret it at all. It's honestly better than my Kiehl's moisturizer and I've been using that one for years.

reviews.headline: Revitalizing moisturizer
reviews.comments: I was using lancome but cannot afford it anymore so I bought this, I love it, my skin looks better!

faceoff_positive.comments:
I have normal skin but since I live in the state of Connecticut; during the fall and winters that quickly changes. Within these seasons most of my face remains normal with the exceptions of dryness around my eyebrow, below my cheeks where contour would normally go, a small area of my chin, and the nostril area of my nose. Other concerns I am currently experiencing are very small fine lines around my forehead and eyes. In the fall I also have little pimples around my nose from dryness. 

Estée Lauder Revitalizing Supreme+ Youth Power Creme Moisturizer is a very thick moisturizer, it has a very subtle floral fragrance that is pleasant, and a few dabs of the moisturizer will go along way so apply very small amounts and work that in before proceeding to add more. Upon application the moisturizer felt a bit oil, even when I applied very little but I was pleasantly surprised to find that it was fully absorbed by my skin with minutes of letting it set. I immediately noticed that my skin was extremely soft, my face felt hydrated, and lifted….much more firm then before the application. Due to it being my first application, I can not see a visible difference in my skin just yet. I can however see that it is hydrated and glowing. Another thing I noticed right away would be that the moisturizer did not irritate my overly sensitive eyes and (I truly appreciate that).

It is a week with Estée Lauder Revitalizing Supreme+ Youth Power Creme Moisturizer and I am in love, my skin is indeed firmer, hydrated, glowing, without irritation, and the moisturizer workers wonders under makeup. In fact, I set out to purchase the entire line!
faceoff_positive.headline: I love it!

faceoff_negative.comments:
I've been using the same product for years and I always buy them from Ulta, they always had a protective layer on the top of the product, so I was just suspected. For the first time I wanted to order on their website( with other stuff, since they had good deals), and I sincerely regretted…  You guys kinda made me feel like disgusted by the brand.

After I received my product, I have realized that one of the cream jars doesn't have a protective lid on it and I tried to ask the customer service to get more information. I kindly asked whether it's normal for the product does not have a protective layer/lid or not. Without she replies to the question she said that, she is going to order a replacement one, and it's gonna be shipped out in 1-2 business days. I accepted, 3 days passes, I contacted the customer service again, and asked what was going on with the order. He asked me what's wrong with the product, and I told him what  the issue was. He said the exact same thing that the previous agent said. I said okay, I'll wait. 2 days passes, nothing heard. Then, I called them. The representative sounded like he was not willing to help me at all. After repeating myself over and over again, he finally understood the problem. With unknown attitude, he said I need to return the product and they can refund the money back. I said, okay please create a return label, and I can take care of it. He said he did, and I will get an email regarding the issue within couple minutes. 
I've been waiting for the further update from them to move forward. While I was waiting, the product was labeled as out of stock. So i had no choice but wait until they ship out the item. 

My question is why you guys don't have any after purchase service? It shouldn't be that hard to communicate with the representative, and shouldn't be that difficult to not being responsive and responsible. I just wanted to ask a very simple and clear question about the item that I ordered, no one answered me properly. They
faceoff_negative.headline: The customer service department is horrible
